cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the design of wireless backhauling network topology and frequency/power allocation on wireless links. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper proposes a mixed-integer-linear-program (MILP) for minimum cost design and a successive inner approximation (SIA)-based design for adjusting transmit power at wireless links. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper proposes a re-tuning algorithm that reacts to changes in network conditions. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper mentions the required rate demand at each base station. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the least likely category as there is no mention of security or cryptography in the paper.
